barrel file and read each component's props.

<!--
Tip for kit authors: replace this content with per-component guidance.

If you\u2019re using npm packages or have generated new components in Make, we recommend adding component guidelines. This way, Make can learn what components are available and how to use them correctly.

Create a file for each component. In each file, cover:
* Usage - When to use the component, including the other components it's commonly used with or within
* Semantic purpose - What each component group means
* Examples\xa0\u2014 Correct and incorrect usage, especially for common mistakes
* API - The API of the component, including its properties

For more tips, check our guide:
https://developers.figma.com/docs/code/write-design-system-guidelines/#components-component-guidelines
-->`,N=`This file documents per-token usage patterns specific to this kit.

If this file is empty or contains only this placeholder, treat the kit's
compiled stylesheet as the source of truth \u2014 see \`/guidelines/setup.md\`
Step 2 for how to enumerate the available CSS custom properties (e.g.
\`--primary-button\`, \`--text-default\`, \`--spacer-md\`). Always use
\`var(--token-name)\` over hardcoded color, spacing, or typography values
so the kit's theming continues to apply.

<!--
Tip for kit authors: replace this content with per-token guidance.

Token guidelines teach Make what tokens are available and how to use them correctly.

Create a file for each token type. In each file, cover:
* Naming pattern\xa0\u2014 How token names are structured so Make can find tokens independently
* Semantic purpose\xa0\u2014 What each token group means (success, neutral, etc.)
* Usage frequency\xa0\u2014 How often each value is used, so the agent knows which are defaults vs. edge cases
* Decision tree\xa0\u2014 A quick lookup the agent can follow to pick the right token
* Examples\xa0\u2014 Correct and incorrect usage, especially for common mistakes

For more tips, check our guide:
https://developers.figma.com/docs/code/write-design-system-guidelines
-->`,w=`**Add your own guidelines here**
<!--

Style guidelines teach Make what styles are available and how to use them correctly.

Focus on visual patterns and spacing. For example:
* Layout principles\xa0- Grid systems, breakpoints, container widths
* Spacing scale\xa0- "Use 4px base unit: 4, 8, 16, 24, 32, 48, 64"
* Typography hierarchy\xa0- Specific font sizes, weights, line heights for h1-h6, body, captions
* Border radius system\xa0- "Cards: 12px, Buttons: 8px, Inputs: 6px"
* Responsive behavior\xa0- "Stack horizontally on desktop, vertically on mobile"

For more tips, check our guide:
